          "Assessment Strategy",
          "Performance Metric: Best Model",
          "Comments",
          "Limitations"
        ],
        [
          "Classification",
          "Intellingent Tutoring System & MOOC",
          "Next Question Being Correct",
          "Correct (1) vs Incorrect (0)",
          "536 Fraction Learners, \n757 TIMSS learners, 2922 ECPE learners, 4217 learners, 1730 Berkeley learners, 58939 Castor learners",
          "Fraction, TIMSS, ECPE, ASSISTments, Castor",
          "Answer Sequences",
          "[Users, Items, Skills, Attempts, Wins and Fails, Extra Side Information - all One Hot Encoded]",
          "Most approaches precedding this model students or questions using unidimensional parameters. Moreover, most approaches are unable to model side information per question (such as multiple skills). ",
          "The Factorization machines approach not only allows a higher dimensionality representation of students/questions but also shows side information is more effective to improve model performance than increasing the latent dimensions. ",
          "The first difference stems from how data is represented: ASSISTments and Berkeley have a temporal representation while the remaining datasets are not. \n\nFeature Encoding requires the consideration of the following dimensions: \n\nUsers, Items, Skills, Attempts, Wins and Fails, Extra Side Information - all One Hot Encoded.\n\nSequences are represented as triplets.",
          "AFM, PFA, IRT, MIRTb10, MIRTb20, KTM(iswf0), KTM(iswf20), KTM(iswfe5)",
          "5-Fold Cross-Validation",
          "ASSISTments\n{AUC: 0.8186 - KTM(iswfe5)}\n\nBerkeley\n{AUC: 0.7780 - KTM(iswfe20)}\n\nECPE\n{AUC: 0.6811 - IRT}\n\nFraction\n{AUC: 0.6672 - MIRTb20}\n\nTIMSS\n{AUC: 0.6946 - IRT}\n\nCastor\n{AUC: 0.7603 - IRT}",
          "The introduction of side information seems to increase the performace of the model. This is increase is more noticeable than augmenting the number of latent dimensions being considered for the knowledge model.\n\nUltimately, KTMs are presented as testbeds for the introduction of additional features.",
          "Encoding (OHE) may need refinement.\n\nNot all models are considered for all datasets."
        ]
      ],
      "index": 5
    }
  ],
